The paper focuses on the interplay between non-functional requirements (NFRs) and builds on continuous integration (CI) systems. This suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) as the primary categories. Additionally, the study involves analyzing data from software projects, which could fall under software development (cs.SD) or machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for tools to improve CI, which could fall under cybernetics (cs.CY).
